    "stay": {
        "title": "Where to stay",
        "description": "The two major axis are Saint-Laurent Boulevard and Sainte-Catherine Street.",
        "hoods": [
            {
                "name": "Plateau-Mont-Royal",
                "mapImage": "plateau.png",
                "corners": [
                    {
                        "se": "Sherbrooke / Papineau",
                        "sw": "Sherbrooke / Parc",
                        "ne": "Rosemont / Papineau",
                        "nw": "Van Horne / Parc"
                    }
                ],
                "about": [
                    "\"Le Plateau\", as Montrealers call it, has become quite the <em>bourgeois</em> neighbourhood. Not that that's a bad thing.",
                    "A lot of people live there, there's a lot of shops and restaurants (on St-Laurent, St-Denis, Mont-Royal, Laurier, mainly), and then a ton of other ones sprinkled everywhere in the middle."
                ]
            },
            {
                "name": "Mile-End",
                "mapImage": "mile-end.png",
                "corners": [
                    {
                        "se": "Henri-Julien / Mont-Royal",
                        "sw": "Hutchison / Mont-Royal",
                        "ne": "Rosemont / Henri-Julien",
                        "nw": "Van Horne / Hutchison"
                    }
                ],
                "about": [
                    "Technically, the Mile-End is part of the Plateau-Mont-Royal neighborhood.",
                    "Historically, it was the jewish neighborhood, then the artist neighbourhood. It has gentrified a biut in the past decade or so, but gladly the city maintains rents low-ish and reserves spaces and buildings even for artists to stay and keep their studios there, and thus keeps this neighborhood's soul in its right place."
                ]
            },
            {
                "name": "Petite Italie / Mile-Ex",
                "mapImage": "petite-italie.png",
                "corners": [
                    {
                        "se": "Van Horne / Saint-Denis",
                        "sw": "Van Horne / Parc",
                        "ne": "Jean-Talon / Saint-Denis",
                        "nw": "Parc / Jean-Talon"
                    }
                ],
                "about": [
                    "Not many italians still living there, apart maybe from the old dudes (they're all dudes) that hang out at Caffè Italia.",
                    "Some more text about the neighbourhood."
                ]
            },
            {
                "name": "Petite Bourgogne",
                "mapImage": "petite-bourgogne.png",
                "corners": [
                    {
                        "se": "Notre-Dame / Guy",
                        "sw": "Atwater / Saint-Ambroise",
                        "ne": "Guy / Saint-Antoine",
                        "nw": "Saint-Antoine / Atwater"
