    "transport": {
        "title": "How to get around",
        "description": "All roads lead somewhere.",
        "service": [
            {
                "name": "STM",
                "type": "The bus and subway service",
                "url": {
                    "text": "stm.info",
                    "link": "http://www.stm.info/en"
                },
                "notes": [
                    "Subway hours are line specific. But generally it's kind of sucky like in Boston: open until 12:00-30 AM on most days, and until 1:00-30 AM on Satudays.",
                    "There is however, and gladly, plenty of 'night' buses."
                ]
            },
            {
                "name": "Bixi",
                "type": "The bikeshare program",
                "url": {
                    "text": "bixi.com",
                    "link": "https://bixi.com/"
                },
                "notes": [
                    "Bixi, Montréal's bike-sharing system, is huge! Lots of people bike in Montréal, and it's quite safe to do so. Probably the one of the safest cities to bike in North America. Lots of bike lanes, etc. But you have to respect the rules and signal properly, etc, becuase people will tell you if you don't, and the police will give you a ticket if you run a red light.",
                    "You'll recognize the bikes as Boston's Hubway uses the same system and bike design.",
                    "The bikes are available from April to November. Then they sleep during the winter."
                ]
            },
